generated_sparql:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX s223: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>
PREFIX s223ex: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223/data/lbnl-example-2#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?zone WHERE {
  ?zone a s223:Zone .
  {
    # Directly associated property
    ?zone s223:hasProperty ?prop .
    ?prop a ?propClass .
    FILTER(?propClass IN (
      s223:QuantifiableObservableProperty,
      s223:QuantifiableActuatableProperty,
      s223:EnumeratedObservableProperty,
      s223:EnumeratedActuatableProperty
    ))
  } UNION {
    # Indirect connection via a RoomDomainSpace
    ?zone s223:hasDomainSpace ?ds .
    ?ds a s223ex:RoomDomainSpace .
    # Follow any number of connection predicates to reach a property
    ?ds ( s223:connected | s223:connectedTo | s223:connectedFrom | s223:connectsThrough | s223:connectedThrough )* ?prop .
    ?prop a ?propClass .
    FILTER(?propClass IN (
      s223:QuantifiableObservableProperty,
      s223:QuantifiableActuatableProperty,
      s223:EnumeratedObservableProperty,
      s223:EnumeratedActuatableProperty
    ))
  }
}

PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/Brick/>
PREFIX std223: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?propertyLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint
WHERE {
  # any building zone
  ?zone a std223:Zone .
  
  # properties that belong to the zone directly or via a domain space (e.g., a room) that the zone encloses
  ?zone (std223:hasProperty | std223:encloses/std223:hasProperty)* ?property .
  
  # humanreadable label of the property
  ?property rdfs:label ?propertyLabel .
  
  # readonly => either no writable flag or explicitly false
  OPTIONAL { ?property brick:writable ?writable . }
  FILTER ( !BOUND(?writable) || ?writable = false )
  
  # external reference(s) attached to the property
  OPTIONAL {
    ?property std223:hasExternalReference ?extRef .
    ?extRef a std223:ExternalReference .
    
    # ALC endpoint  identified by the generic Brick endpoint property and alc in the string
    OPTIONAL { ?extRef brick:endpoint ?alcEndpoint . FILTER(CONTAINS(LCASE(STR(?alcEndpoint)), "alc")) }
    
    # MPC endpoint  stored using the Brick mpc_db_name predicate
    OPTIONAL { ?extRef brick:mpc_db_name ?mpcEndpoint . }
  }
}
LIMIT 100
